<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-08-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-08-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="25" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                        <head>25. Memorandum from President <persName corresp="#p_KJF_1">Kennedy</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_BM_1">Bundy</persName>,
                            August 7<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d25fn1">Presidential approval
                                on lifting laboratory experiments to one ton. Secret. 1 p. Kennedy
                                Library, National Security Files, Subjects Series, Nuclear Testing,
                                7/16/61–8/9/61.</note></head>
                        <dateline>
                            <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" when="1961-08-07">August 7, 1961</date>
                        </dateline>
                        <pb facs="d25-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d25-1"/>
                        <p><persName corresp="#p_SGT_1">Seaborg</persName> recommends that we lift
                            our laboratory experiments to one ton in his letter of August 4th. It
                            seems to me that we should consider that.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>J.K.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>